cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper focuses on data-efficient optimization for robotics problems, which is a core topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves using a sequential variational autoencoder to embed simulated trajectories into a lower-dimensional space, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). Bayesian optimization is also a key component of the approach, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve hardware and simulation experiments with robots, which is a systems and control topic (cs.SY), and also involve comparisons to several baselines, which is a computer vision topic (cs.CV).
